The sailors, in tasselled caps of red worsted, were getting the heavy tackles 
in readiness for the whales. But they worked rather slow and talked very fast, 
and seemed in anything but a good humor. All their noses upwardly projected 
from their faces like so many jib-booms. Now and then pairs of them would drop 
their work, and run up to the mast-head to get some fresh air. Some thinking 
